<h1 id="installation">Installation</h1>
<p>You need to have <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/how-to-clone-only-a-subdirectory-with-git-or-svn/">git</a> installed.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">git clone https://github/terroo/aptporn
<span class="nb">cd </span>aptporn/
sh aptporn <span class="nt">--install</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Before, it is also legal to run the command: <code class="highlighter-rouge">./aptporn --update</code> to update your entire system. For more details, run: <code class="highlighter-rouge">./aptporn --help</code>.</p>

<h1 id="bspwm-shortcuts-"><a href="https://github.com/baskerville/bspwm">Bspwm</a> shortcuts :</h1>

<ul>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">Super + Alt + q</code> - Closes the session</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">Super + Esc</code> - refreshes bspwm and Polybar</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">Super + d</code> - Opens the Rofi</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">Super + enter</code> - Opens the terminal</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">Super + w</code> - Close a window</li>
</ul>

<p>And among other commands that can be consulted in the video below</p>

